uage popular culture, swearing in multiple languages, and turn-final code-switching to English to signal the punchline.The book will appeal to readers interested in humor, comics, or how linguistic innovation, language play, and language contact each can further the modern development of language, exemplified by the case of Swedish.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aComic books, strips, etc.-Sweden. 0aSwedish wit and humor, Pictorial. 4aComics. 4aHumor. 4aLinguistik. 4aSchweden. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aComics.  aHumor.  aLinguistics.  aSweden.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Frontlist 2020z978311074316608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015050580 cprintz978150151431940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150511940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501505119423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501505119/original  a978-3-11-065906-1  De Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCb2020  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  a978-3-11-069628-8  DG Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3